# Ollama Modelfile for Bonsai-8B — the single on-device model used by
# the KChat SLM demo. Creates a local alias `bonsai-8b` matching the
# app's default `MODEL_NAME` (the bootstrap wires exactly one on-device
# adapter; there is no separate tier split).
#
# Source: https://huggingface.co/prism-ml/Bonsai-8B-gguf
#
# The canonical x86 CPU artifact is `Bonsai-8B-Q1_0.gguf` (~1.16 GB on
# disk). Q1_0 is PrismML's 1-bit quant; the PrismML llama.cpp fork
# ships an x86 SIMD kernel for it (AVX2/FMA), so on commodity x86 hosts
# this is the fastest CPU artifact (~11 tok/s on 8 vCPU EPYC vs the
# ~0.45 tok/s scalar fallback Q2_0 hits on the same box). On ARM /
# Apple Silicon, the `Ternary-Bonsai-8B-Q2_0.gguf` file is the faster
# option — see `docs/cpu-perf-tuning.md` for the per-arch kernel
# coverage table.
#
# Ollama's `hf.co/<user>/<repo>:<quant>` shorthand does NOT accept
# `Q1_0`, so the Modelfile references the file by local path.
# `scripts/setup-models.sh` downloads `Bonsai-8B-Q1_0.gguf` next to
# this Modelfile if it isn't already present.
#
# Usage:
#   ./scripts/setup-models.sh
# or, manually:
#   curl -L -o models/Bonsai-8B-Q1_0.gguf \
#     https://huggingface.co/prism-ml/Bonsai-8B-gguf/resolve/main/Bonsai-8B-Q1_0.gguf
#   ollama create bonsai-8b -f models/Modelfile.bonsai8b
#
# Note: stock Ollama 0.22.x can `create` an alias from this file but
# CANNOT run inference against it (the bundled `llama.cpp` does not
# implement the Q1_0 tensor type). The CPU-only demo path uses the
# PrismML `llama.cpp` fork — see `docs/cpu-perf-tuning.md`.

FROM ./Bonsai-8B-Q1_0.gguf

PARAMETER temperature 0.7
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
# num_ctx: attention cost scales with context window, so a larger
# window slows every token on CPU-only hosts. 2048 covers most KChat
# task prompts (256–1024 input, 32–256 output) while keeping CPU-only
# inference tractable on the 8GB shared VM the demo targets. Raise to
# 4096 or 8192 only when running on GPU / Metal / NPU where KV-cache
# bandwidth is cheap. See docs/cpu-perf-tuning.md for the full
# context / thread / mlock / no-mmap tuning matrix.
PARAMETER num_ctx 2048

SYSTEM """You are a helpful AI assistant inside KChat. You run on-device for privacy. Keep responses concise and actionable."""
